        "jsCode": "const input = $('Разбираем входные данные').item.json\nconst verifyTaskKey = `verify-${Date.now().toString(36)}-${Math.random().toString(36).slice(2, 8)}`\n\nconst verifyPrompt = `VERIFICATION TASK — verify that the implementation meets acceptance criteria.\n\nORIGINAL TASK:\n${input.originalPrompt}\n\nACCEPTANCE CRITERIA:\n${input.acceptanceCriteria}\n\nRESULT OF EXECUTION:\n${input.resultText}\n\nGo through EACH acceptance criterion ONE BY ONE. For each:\n- Criterion: restate the exact criterion\n- Evidence: what you observed\n- Verdict: PASS or FAIL\n- Reason: why\n\nThen output:\nVERIFICATION: PASSED | FAILED\nISSUES: (list if any)\n\nDo NOT change code. You are a verifier, not a fixer.`\n\nconst contextJson = JSON.stringify({\n  source: 'verification',\n  newSessionRequested: true,\n  original_parent_task_key: input.parentTaskKey || input.taskKey,\n  original_parent_session_id: input.parentSessionId || input.sessionId,\n  original_parent_prompt: input.parentOriginalPrompt || input.originalPrompt,\n  acceptanceCriteria: input.acceptanceCriteria,\n  originalPrompt: input.originalPrompt,\n})\n\nreturn { json: { verifyTaskKey, verifyPrompt, contextJson, chatId: input.chatId, workerAlias: input.workerAlias, taskKey: input.taskKey } }"
